  "local_port": 37744,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good movies about a person that has a hidden power that he/she couldn't use until put into a pressure situation?",
  "response": "There are numerous compelling movies that feature characters with hidden or latent powers that only surface under pressure or in critical moments. Here are some notable examples:\n\n1. **The Matrix (1999)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Neo (Keanu Reeves) leads an ordinary life until he is drawn into the mysterious world of the Matrix. Under intense pressure and dire circumstances, Neo discovers his extraordinary ability to manipulate the simulated reality, ultimately realizing he is \"The One\" destined to bring an end to the war between humans and machines.\n   \n2. **Unbreakable (2000)**\n   - **Synopsis:** In this thriller directed by M. Night Shyamalan, David Dunn (Bruce Willis) survives a devastating train crash with no injuries. As he grapples with this miracle, he begins to uncover his own superhuman strength and resilience, realizing he might possess abilities far beyond those of an ordinary man.\n   \n3. **Chronicle (2012)**\n   - **Synopsis:** This found-footage-style film follows three high school friends who gain telekinetic powers after encountering a mysterious substance. Their abilities emerge and escalate during high-stress situations, leading to both thrilling and destructive consequences as they struggle to control their newfound powers.\n   \n4. **Doctor Strange (2016)**\n   - **Synopsis:** After a tragic accident ends his career as a neurosurgeon, Stephen Strange (Benedict Cumberbatch) seeks healing and discovers the hidden world of magic and alternate dimensions. Under immense personal and external pressures, he unlocks powerful mystical abilities, ultimately becoming a master sorcerer.\n   \n5. **X-Men Series**\n   - **Synopsis:** Across the various films in the X-Men franchise, numerous mutants discover and harness their unique powers, often triggered by high-stress situations. Characters like Wolverine, Jean Grey, and Storm showcase their abilities when faced with intense challenges, highlighting themes of identity and control.\n   \n6. **Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse (2018)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Miles Morales, a teenager who gains spider-like abilities, initially struggles to control his powers. When confronted with life-threatening situations, his latent potential emerges fully, enabling him to become Spider-Man and save multiple dimensions.\n   \n7. **Limitless (2011)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Eddie Morra (Bradley Cooper) discovers a mysterious drug that enhances his cognitive abilities to superhuman levels. Under the pressure of high-stakes financial and personal challenges, his hidden intellectual and strategic powers are unleashed, transforming his life in unexpected ways.\n   \n8. **Harry Potter Series**\n   - **Synopsis:** Throughout the series, Harry Potter discovers and hones his magical abilities, often revealing new powers and strengths in response to escalating threats from dark forces. Critical moments, such as battles against Voldemort, force him to fully embrace and utilize his magical potential.\n   \n9. **Frozen (2013)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Although animated, Elsa's journey in \"Frozen\" embodies the theme of hidden power. Her ability to create ice and snow is initially uncontrollable and hidden, but under emotional and physical pressure, especially during the climax, she unleashes her powers fully, leading to both conflict and resolution.\n   \n10. **Jumper (2008)**\n    - **Synopsis:** David (Hayden Christensen) discovers he can teleport, a power he initially uses selfishly. When pursued by those who aim to control or eliminate \"jumpers,\" David must fully embrace and master his teleportation abilities to survive and protect others.\n\nThese films explore the theme of latent abilities awakening in characters when faced with significant challenges or high-pressure situations. They offer a mix of superhero action, psychological drama, and thrilling narratives that highlight personal growth and the responsible use of power.",
